<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-04-26"><hi rend="italic">April 26,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has read with pleasure the
                            announcement contained in your dispatch No. 136, of the 16th ultimo, of
                            the resumption of diplomatic relations between the Argentine Republic
                            and Uruguay.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>